<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="In_animation">In animation</span></h2>
<figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Rusted_Shield_anime.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/9/97/Rusted_Shield_anime.png/250px-Rusted_Shield_anime.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="250" height="141" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/9/97/Rusted_Shield_anime.png/375px-Rusted_Shield_anime.png 1.5x, https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/9/97/Rusted_Shield_anime.png/500px-Rusted_Shield_anime.png 2x" data-file-width="1280" data-file-height="720" /></a><figcaption>The Rusted Shield in <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Journeys:_The_Series" title="Pokémon Journeys: The Series"><i>Pokémon Journeys: The Series</i></a></figcaption></figure>
<h3><span id="Pok.C3.A9mon_the_Series"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Pokémon_the_Series"><i>Pokémon the Series</i></span></h3>
<h4><span id="Pok.C3.A9mon_Journeys:_The_Series"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Pokémon_Journeys:_The_Series"><a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Journeys:_The_Series" title="Pokémon Journeys: The Series"><i>Pokémon Journeys: The Series</i></a></span></h4>
<p>In <i><a href="/wiki/JN044" title="JN044">Sword and Shield: "From Here to Eternatus!"</a></i>, <a href="/wiki/Goh" title="Goh">Goh</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sonia" title="Sonia">Sonia</a> found the Rusted Shield at the altar in the <a href="/wiki/Slumbering_Weald" title="Slumbering Weald">Slumbering Weald</a> after requesting the help of <a href="/wiki/Zacian_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zacian (Pokémon)">Zacian</a> and <a href="/wiki/Zamazenta_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zamazenta (Pokémon)">Zamazenta</a> in dealing with the <a href="/wiki/Darkest_Day" title="Darkest Day">Darkest Day</a>. Goh collected it and the <a href="/wiki/Rusted_Sword" title="Rusted Sword">Rusted Sword</a> and took both items with him. In <i><a href="/wiki/JN045" title="JN045">Sword and Shield... The Legends Awaken!</a></i>, the Rusted Shield called forth Zamazenta to the <a href="/wiki/Tower_summit" title="Tower summit">tower summit</a>, who grabbed the Shield in its mouth, allowing it to transform into its <a href="/wiki/List_of_Pok%C3%A9mon_with_form_differences#Zacian_and_Zamazenta" title="List of Pokémon with form differences">Crowned Shield</a> form. After Goh caught <a href="/wiki/Goh%27s_Eternatus" class="mw-redirect" title="Goh&#39;s Eternatus">Eternatus</a>, Zamazenta left its Shield behind. <a href="/wiki/Ash_Ketchum" title="Ash Ketchum">Ash</a> and Goh were later seen returning the Rusted Sword and Shield where they once rested.
</p>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<h3><span id="Pok.C3.A9mon_Evolutions"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Pokémon_Evolutions">Pokémon Evolutions</span></h3>
<figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Rusted_Sword_Shield_Evolutions.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/4/4e/Rusted_Sword_Shield_Evolutions.png/250px-Rusted_Sword_Shield_Evolutions.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="250" height="106" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/4/4e/Rusted_Sword_Shield_Evolutions.png/375px-Rusted_Sword_Shield_Evolutions.png 1.5x, https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/4/4e/Rusted_Sword_Shield_Evolutions.png/500px-Rusted_Sword_Shield_Evolutions.png 2x" data-file-width="1280" data-file-height="542" /></a><figcaption>The Rusted Shield in <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Evolutions" title="Pokémon Evolutions">Pokémon Evolutions</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>The Rusted Shield appeared in a flashback in <i><a href="/wiki/PE01" title="PE01">The Champion</a></i>, under the possession of <a href="/wiki/Hop" title="Hop">Hop</a>. When he held it up during his and <a href="/wiki/Victor_(game)" title="Victor (game)">Victor</a>'s battle against <a href="/wiki/Eternatus_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Eternatus (Pokémon)">Eternatus</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Tower_summit" title="Tower summit">tower summit</a>, it summoned <a href="/wiki/Zamazenta_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zamazenta (Pokémon)">Zamazenta</a> to their aid and allowed it to transform into its <a href="/wiki/List_of_Pok%C3%A9mon_with_form_differences#Zacian_and_Zamazenta" title="List of Pokémon with form differences">Crowned Shield</a> form.
</p>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="In_the_manga">In the manga</span></h2>
<figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Rusted_Sword_Shield_Adventures.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/2/2d/Rusted_Sword_Shield_Adventures.png/200px-Rusted_Sword_Shield_Adventures.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="200" height="186" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/2/2d/Rusted_Sword_Shield_Adventures.png/300px-Rusted_Sword_Shield_Adventures.png 1.5x, https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/2/2d/Rusted_Sword_Shield_Adventures.png/400px-Rusted_Sword_Shield_Adventures.png 2x" data-file-width="409" data-file-height="380" /></a><figcaption>The Rusted Shield in <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Adventures" title="Pokémon Adventures">Pokémon Adventures</a></figcaption></figure>
<h3><span id="Pok.C3.A9mon_Adventures"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Pokémon_Adventures">Pokémon Adventures</span></h3>
<h4><span id="Sword_.26_Shield_arc"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Sword_&amp;_Shield_arc"><a href="/wiki/Sword_%26_Shield_arc_(Adventures)" title="Sword &amp; Shield arc (Adventures)"><i>Sword &amp; Shield</i> arc</a></span></h4>
<p>The Rusted Shield first appeared in a flashback in <i><a href="/wiki/PASS05" title="PASS05">Ooh Shiny!! Legendary Equipment</a></i>, along with the Rusted Sword. One year earlier, <a href="/wiki/Henry_Sword" title="Henry Sword">Henry</a>, accompanied by <a href="/wiki/Casey_Shield" title="Casey Shield">Casey</a>, entered <a href="/wiki/Slumbering_Weald" title="Slumbering Weald">Slumbering Weald</a> in order to see the two legendary artifacts. After confronting illusions of <a href="/wiki/Zacian_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zacian (Pokémon)">Zacian</a> and <a href="/wiki/Zamazenta_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zamazenta (Pokémon)">Zamazenta</a> at the altar at the end of the forest and convincing them they weren't trying to steal anything, the two <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Trainer" title="Pokémon Trainer">Trainers</a> approached the two artifacts on the altar, but were then knocked out by a bright burst of light. When they recovered, the artifacts were gone.
</p><p>In <i><a href="/wiki/PASS20" title="PASS20">Cracking!! Brilliant Tap-Dancing</a></i>, it was revealed that the artifacts had been stolen by <a href="/wiki/Sordward" title="Sordward">Sordward</a> and <a href="/wiki/Shielbert" title="Shielbert">Shielbert</a>. In <i><a href="/wiki/PASS26" title="PASS26">Cracked!! The Rusted Sword and Shield</a></i>, they used the artifacts to "prove" themselves as descendants of Galar's ancient heroes. When the two brothers took on <a href="/wiki/Eternatus_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Eternatus (Pokémon)">Eternatus</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Tower_summit" title="Tower summit">tower summit</a>, they took out the artifacts, but nothing happened, and the items were sent flying to the moat surrounding the <a href="/wiki/Hammerlocke_Stadium" title="Hammerlocke Stadium">Hammerlocke Stadium</a>, from which they were recovered by Casey's <a href="/wiki/Falinks_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Falinks (Pokémon)">Falinks</a> and <a href="/wiki/Stunfisk_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Stunfisk (Pokémon)">Stunfisk</a> and taken to her, who gave them to Henry to clean and repair. However, to his horror, Henry soon realized that he could not forge and repair the artifacts. In <i><a href="/wiki/PASS30" title="PASS30">Oh My!! The Disappearance of Henry</a></i>, the artifacts, along with Henry, disappeared as Zacian and Zamazenta attacked Eternatus, getting <a href="/wiki/Teleport_(move)" title="Teleport (move)">teleported</a> away by an unseen Pokémon. Casey later discovered that the artifacts had wound up in two different places: the <a href="/wiki/Isle_of_Armor" title="Isle of Armor">Isle of Armor</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Crown_Tundra" title="Crown Tundra">Crown Tundra</a>.
</p><p>In <i><a href="/wiki/PASS37" title="PASS37">Crackle!! Retrieve the Sword &amp; Shield</a></i>, the Rusted Shield was revealed to have been found by <a href="/wiki/Galarian_form" title="Galarian form">Galarian</a> <a href="/wiki/Moltres_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Moltres (Pokémon)">Moltres</a> and hidden at <a href="/wiki/Loop_Lagoon" title="Loop Lagoon">Loop Lagoon</a>. Henry was able to reclaim the artifact from Moltres shortly before it grabbed him and took him to the Crown Tundra, where he later successfully purified it of Eternatus's poison. In <i><a href="/wiki/PASS41" title="PASS41">Shing!! Final Form</a></i>, Zamazenta used the shield to transform to its <a href="/wiki/List_of_Pok%C3%A9mon_with_form_differences#Zacian_and_Zamazenta" title="List of Pokémon with form differences">Crowned Shield</a> form.
</p>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="In_the_TCG">In the TCG</span></h2>
<figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:RustedShieldShiningFates61.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c7/RustedShieldShiningFates61.jpg/200px-RustedShieldShiningFates61.jpg" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="200" height="279" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c7/RustedShieldShiningFates61.jpg/300px-RustedShieldShiningFates61.jpg 1.5x, https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c7/RustedShieldShiningFates61.jpg/400px-RustedShieldShiningFates61.jpg 2x" data-file-width="660" data-file-height="920" /></a><figcaption>The Rusted Shield in the TCG</figcaption></figure>
<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href="/wiki/Rusted_Shield_(Shining_Fates_61)" title="Rusted Shield (Shining Fates 61)">Rusted Shield (Shining Fates 61)</a></i></dd></dl>
<p>The <b>Rusted Shield</b> was introduced as a <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Tool_card_(TCG)" title="Pokémon Tool card (TCG)">Pokémon Tool card</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Trading_Card_Game" title="Pokémon Trading Card Game">Pokémon Trading Card Game</a> during the English Sword &amp; Shield Series (the Japanese Sword &amp; Shield Era). It was first released in the Japanese <a href="/wiki/Shiny_Star_V_(TCG)" class="mw-redirect" title="Shiny Star V (TCG)">Shiny Star V</a> expansion before debuting in English in the <a href="/wiki/Shining_Fates_(TCG)" title="Shining Fates (TCG)">Shining Fates</a> expansion, with artwork by <a href="/wiki/5ban_Graphics" title="5ban Graphics">5ban Graphics</a>. It allows <a href="/wiki/Zamazenta_(TCG)#Zamazenta_V" title="Zamazenta (TCG)">Zamazenta V</a> to gain 70 HP.
</p>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Trivia">Trivia</span></h2>
<ul><li>While the <a href="/wiki/Player_character" title="Player character">player</a> seemingly obtains this item in <a href="/wiki/Slumbering_Weald" title="Slumbering Weald">Slumbering Weald</a> during the climax of <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Sword_and_Shield" title="Pokémon Sword and Shield">Pokémon Shield</a>, this is not the case, as the game simply tells the player they obtained it without them actually obtaining anything.</li></ul>
